article.headline: Siena 66, St. Peter's 50
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP)-Kenny Hasbrouck scored 17 points to lead Siena past St. Peter's 66-50 in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Sunday afternoon. Siena (13-10, 8-5 MAAC) held St. Peter's scoreless for the final 8:45 of the first half, using a 14-0 run to take a 38-25 lead. The Peacocks (3-19, 1-11) cut the gap to 52-45 with 5:54 left in the game on an Akeem Gooding free throw, but could get no closer. The Saints used a 14-3 run to take their largest lead, 66-48 with 1:42 to go. St. Peters, which has lost 14 in a row to match its longest losing streak on record, shot just 10-25 from the field, while Siena went 13-24. Tay Fisher came off the bench to score 11 points for Siena. Raul Orta led St. Peter's with 12 points. Gooding had 10 points and eight rebounds.
